<div class="art-Post-inner art-article">
<h2 class="art-PostHeaderIcon-wrapper">
  <img src="http://www.organicgourmetcoffeestore.com/ad/wp-content/themes/adBlueRounded/images/PostHeaderIcon.png" width="29" height="21" alt="" />
<span class="art-PostHeader"><a href="http://www.organicgourmetcoffeestore.com/ad/find-dark-chocolate-cocoa-benefits/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Find Out About Dark Chocolate Cocoa Benefits">
Find Out About Dark Chocolate Cocoa Benefits</a></span>
</h2>
<div class="art-PostMetadataHeader">
<div class="art-PostHeaderIcons art-metadata-icons">
<img src="http://www.organicgourmetcoffeestore.com/ad/wp-content/themes/adBlueRounded/images/PostDateIcon.png" width="16" height="16" alt="" />
September 10th, 2010 | Author: <a href="#" title="Author">coffeexpert</a>

</div>

</div>
<div class="art-PostContent">
<p>Probably the most commonly held perception of chocolate is that it tastes good but is not exactly good for your health or weight. However, there are studies that would indicate at least for cocoa and dark chocolate that they actually enhance the health of your body. For your heart to be able to function at it&#8217;s best it needs for your arteries to be flexible, open and free from blockages. It was found that these two substances play an important role in proper heart functioning. How is that for a <a href="http://www.organicgourmetcoffeestore.com/ad/find-place-tasty-chocolate-gift/" >tasty chocolate gift</a></p>
<p>Healthy Cardiovascular System</p>
<p>The truth of the fact is that dark chocolate and cocoa both help in maintaining a healthy cardiovascular system as they help to keep the blood flowing normally and they also help in keeping blood pressure under control. In fact, cocoa <a href="http://www.organicgourmetcoffeestore.com/?page_id=28" >chocolate beverages</a> in particular helps in maintaining arteries and ensures that they always remain in good health.</p>
<p>Even when tests have been conducted regarding the effectiveness of dark chocolate and cocoa it has been found that after consuming dark chocolate or cocoa blood pressure cam down to manageable levels and flow of blood normalized as well. Besides enjoying the delicious taste of dark chocolate and cocoa, you also get significant health benefits and this has been confirmed by many tests that have been conducted over the past few decades.</p>
<p>Certainly, more research is required about the many benefits of consuming dark chocolate and cocoa; especially, the long term effects on people suffering from high blood pressure. What is known for sure is that dark chocolate and cocoa help in relaxing and widening the arteries help in preventing build-up of plaque that could otherwise have blocked arteries, and they also play an important role in preventing blood from clotting up.</p>
<p>The power of dark chocolate and cocoa seems to lie in the fact that both contain high amounts of antioxidants which in turn are known as polyphenols that are beneficial to a person’s health. In fact, dark chocolate cocoa also contain flavanols that are very important to maintaining a healthy heart and it is these flavanols that help in rendering useless unstable molecules (also known as free radicals).</p>
<p>For those who are interested in the nuts and bolts of dark chocolates, there is a lot of information available that deals with things such as dark chocolate nutrition that can help you understand just what is contained in your dark chocolate bar and how the ingredients will affect your health.</p>
<p>Of course the idea is to eat dark chocolate in reasonable quantities. This will ensure that you receive the health benefits that it can give you. These benefits include better circulation of blood through the arteries and minimizing the risk of heart disease.</p>

</div>
