<h2 class="art-PostHeaderIcon-wrapper">
  <img src="http://www.organicgourmetcoffeestore.com/ad/wp-content/themes/adBlueRounded/images/PostHeaderIcon.png" width="29" height="21" alt="" />
<span class="art-PostHeader"><a href="http://www.organicgourmetcoffeestore.com/ad/guide-milk-free-chocolate/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to A Guide To Milk Free Chocolate">
A Guide To Milk Free Chocolate</a></span>
</h2>
<div class="art-PostMetadataHeader">
<div class="art-PostHeaderIcons art-metadata-icons">
<img src="http://www.organicgourmetcoffeestore.com/ad/wp-content/themes/adBlueRounded/images/PostDateIcon.png" width="16" height="16" alt="" />
September 10th, 2010 | Author: <a href="#" title="Author">coffeexpert</a>

</div>

</div>
<div class="art-PostContent">
<p>You may have heard a lot about organic milk chocolate, regular milk chocolate and <a href="http://www.organicgourmetcoffeestore.com/ad/find-dark-chocolate-cocoa-benefits/" >dark chocolate cocoa benefits</a> but have you even heard of milk free chocolate? The first thing that crosses your mind is why? This is a perfect solution for people with a milk allergy. You can now enjoy chocolate again because you don&#8217;t have to worry about the after effects.</p>
<p>Information On The Details</p>
<p>Milk free chocolate is, quite simply, chocolate that is made without the use of milk. This means that even people who are lactose intolerant can enjoy these <a href="http://www.organicgourmetcoffeestore.com/?page_id=28" >chocolate beverages</a> without worry, which is really fantastic news. No matter what type of chocolate recipe you are preparing you can replace the regular chocolate with milk free chocolate if you are going to be serving it to people with food allergies.</p>
<p>How To Purchase It</p>
<p>If you are interested in getting milk free chocolate, there are a couple of companies in particular that you are going to want to check out. One is the Plamil Foods Company, a company which has been making its own chocolate for decades. Their expertise in making quality chocolates ensures that you always get the best of the best each and every time.</p>
<p>In addition to being completely dairy and gluten free, their bars are now manufactured in their ‘no nuts used here’ factory. This way, no matter what food allergies you may have, you will be able to feel safe eating their chocolate and actually enjoy it without having to worry about an ingredient being in there that you are not aware of and which you are not supposed to eat.</p>
<p>Their alternative to milk chocolate has all of the special qualities that you are looking for and plus even more soy to make this bar ideal for those who love the taste of regular dairy milk chocolate but who are unable to consume dairy milk.</p>
<p>They love making fine chocolate with the good nutritional properties of cocoa, but want to make sure that even those with food allergies are able to eat their chocolate bars.</p>
<p>You will also find that a great company to find milk free chocolate product is the Nestle chocolate company. You may have heard of them before since they have been around for years and have built up quite a reputation. They also offer milk free products. Since they do extensive research concerning foods they offer the same degree of expertise around chocolate. There philosophy is that all food has a role in a complete balanced diet. Because of their scientific resources they develop new food products all the time.</p>

</div>
